sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45222
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Vector to transfect Physcomitrella patens with 2 fluorescent proteins [mCherry and mCitrine] activated by dry-shock, through homologous recombination.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Justin Marriott

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45220
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A homologous, though incomplete, section of the PpRac-1 gene to be used as the 5' boundary of our vector to facilitate homologous recombination in Physcomitrella patens.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Justin Marriott

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45211
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This DNA sequence is a native promoter region in Physcomitrella patens for a dehydrin protein. Dehydrin proteins are produced when drought stress or salt stress occurs within an organism. The exact mechanism of this promoter is not known, however it has been validated in the literature as a promoter region for a dehydrin protein in Physcomitrella patens.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cody Maughan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Zolotarov, Y. and Str??mvik, M. (2015). De Novo Regulatory Motif Discovery Identifies Significant Motifs in Promoters of Five Classes of Plant Dehydrin Genes. PLoS One, 10 (6).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The promoter was assumed to be the 1000 bp directly before the transcription start site of the dehydrin gene.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M45214
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence is the DNA sequence between the transcription start and translation start sites on a dehydrin protein gene found in P. patens. While it is true that this entire sequence may not be involved in ribosome binding, it is clear that this sequence contains key elements for ribosome binding and even more specifically a ribosome binding site that is native to P. patens.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Cody Maughan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: From genbank: Physcomitrella patens subsp. patens predicted protein (PHYPADRAFT_173331) mRNA, complete cds.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Only the sequence between the transcription and translation start sites were taken into consideration.

sbol:SequenceAnnotation.dcterms:title: Possible Ribosome Binding Site (right before translation start)
